description.narrative: The CPHA team successfully leveraged partnerships, human and financial resources to advance quality programming, generate evidence, and advocate for the centrality of children’s and women’s protection in complex emergencies. UNICEF provided thought leadership in MHPSS,GBV,Children and Armed Conflict, PSEA and provided operational leadership, such as the emergency child protection operation for children separated from families during evacuation from Afghanistan. The Alliance’s growth continued, with 180,000+ users, underscoring the value of this KM platform. Norway’s flexible support enabled the CPHA team to claim progress across all the CCCs, while key partners (US, Sweden, Germany, Netherlands) deepened their investment in critical priorities | Status:Met | As-of Date:03/03/2022
